result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Shane Michael Molitor was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Shane Michael Molitor was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 9:23 AM. Defendant Shane Michael Molitor in court, in custody. Special appearance by Attorney Jane Bucher.  Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant needs to complete forms for public defender eligibility.  Defendant has been provided criminal complaint in matter.  Court reads charge portion of criminal complaint onto record.  Defendant does understand the charges.  Court has reviewed criminal complaint and it does state probable cause.  State requesting Cash Bond in the amount of $250.00 with conditions.  Attorney Bucher argues, stating signature bond would be sufficient.  State argues this is Defendant's 2nd OWI, and is concerned regarding Defendant appearing for future Court dates.  Court will Order Signature Bond in the amount of $1,000.00 with conditions stated on record.  Court also orders Defendant to keep address current with the Court and DA.  Court vacates warrant.
